1. Changed a few functions in the files I attached so that dojox.gfx can be collapsed.

2. Compiled with VERBOSE.  No crash.  File ran without errors.

3. Compiled with VERBOSE + --debug true.  File doesn't run -- exception on browser.  Open file and see all local variable/argument names messed up.  Variables so messed up that they conflict with other function/global variable names, so it doesn't run.

Behavior: for example, a function:

function hello(world, abc) {
   var test = abc(world);
   world = test;
}

May become:

function $something$completely$different$$ ($del$, $clear156$) {
   var $tmp_may_conflict_with_other_names$ = $clear156$($del$);
   $del$ = $tmp_may_conflict_with_other_names$;
}

Notice that the variable names show up in *other* functions.  Normally it should be something like:

function $hello$$($world123$, $abc456$) {
   var $test$ = $abc456$($world123$);
   $world123$ = $test$;
}
